Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.27,0:01:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,have Nico chant and we'll conclude with personal interviews anybody who wants to\Ntalk to us can we'll give you an individual answer we've got to meet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.69,0:01:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody get to sign anything you want signed just two other things I wanted to\Nfinish off the intellectual history of mankind you see the really decisive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.75,0:01:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual discussion ended in 350 BC all the rhetoric that you see out about\Npolitics and all it's a good time to review Socrates Plato and and the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.81,0:01:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest thinking throughout mankind I happen to have a set of the great books\Nof the Western world it was published in the 30s University of Chicago a world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of scholars there is currently a world collection of scholars\Nthat supports the study a true liberal education is to know the great books of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.23,0:02:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the Western world and they suggest you do it over a 10-year period\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.03,0:02:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a misspent youth as I have told before the spiritual experiences began\Nat age very early age three and age three out of nothingness out of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.02,0:02:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness out of the oblivion of nothingness suddenly there was a\Ncrashing stunning confrontation with existence I was not pleased not only did
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.27,0:02:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you come back into existence but a body went with it\NOn top of that stunning fate, the minute there was the awareness of existence, all this happened
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,non-verbally.\NA three-year-old doesn't know such words as existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.23,0:03:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner was there the stunning awareness of existence than instantly there was the\Nfear of non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.70,0:03:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had come into existence, then it could have been that I would not have come into\Nexistence and the initial confrontation, the initial duality, polarity was existence versus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.26,0:03:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence, whether the infinite reality is void, voidness or allness.\NHaving come out of the pathway of negation, each lifetime would end, I would end up in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.94,0:03:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the void because that which you hold in mind is what you experience and if you think the\Nvoid is the ultimate reality, that's what you experience is void.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if void were the ultimate reality, you could stay there.\NIt's not the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.01,0:03:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Allness is the ultimate reality.\NSo out of nothingness, one comes back in to correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.53,0:04:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't correct itself to consciousness level 850, transcend the duality of divinity\Nas allness or nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of a mistranslation of the teaching of the Buddha, no-thingness, emptiness means\Ndevoid of form, devoid of form, devoid of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.27,0:04:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be no knowingness of the devoid of form.\NOf that which is without form, other than consciousness, because without consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be knowing the void?\NAnyway, the best thinking throughout all of time, which people would like to disregard
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in certain, in present society, the best thinkingness of all time.\NSo democracy is built on the best thinkingness of all time and evolved through the French
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.87,0:05:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophers.\NIt calibrates around 450, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.10,0:05:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the best thinkingness.\N460 is excellence, intellectual excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One has mastered the physical domain at 460.\NSo you see Thomas Aquinas, 460, Aristotle, 498, St. Augustine, 503, you see Chaucer,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.40,0:05:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,480.\NAnd then there's Dantès, 455.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And Dante, I haven't had a chance to research Dante, how he knew what hell was like, because\Nhis description of hell was unbelievably accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.26,0:06:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't know how he knew that, but he's at 505, which is rather unusual.\NYou see Engels is at 200, Dostoevsky, 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes is 470.\NDescartes I refer to in my own writings, because he discerned res interna, from res externa,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.02,0:06:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the subjective from the ostensibly objective.\NSpiritual work is shifting from perceiving thinking reality as something out there, to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.48,0:06:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,realizing that it is only subjectivity that says there's something out there, and the\Nirreducible reality is radical subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.34,0:06:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very familiar idea.\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.86,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only because I say it is that it has any chance to be is, is.\NOtherwise, isn't this, you see, is a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.16,0:06:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this is a concept.\NAll right, so Descartes played an extremely important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin's theory of evolution we already handled this morning\Nbecause at 450 it looks like a dualistic Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.17,0:07:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is also the limitation of theology\Nwhich sees God as first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.53,0:07:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, first cause.\NThere is no such thing as first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.93,0:07:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.15,0:07:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NThere ain't no such thing as first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That which always existed can only have a first cause.\NPlus, it's trying to project the Newtonian paradigm of cause
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.06,0:07:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the infinite, nonlinear,\Nwhich there is no such thing as cause and effect in the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alwaysness has no beginning, so there's no first cause.\NTo be explained because nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.54,0:07:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is what it is and it unfolds out of divinity.\NSo, anyway, that's beyond these people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.22,0:07:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we have Euclid.\NWe've got all the great names, Faraday, the great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see there's a reason we're going to go over this.\NFreud, you see, stops at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud was limited to the scientific paradigm.\NAnd I, at one time, was exactly the same place Freud was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My analysts and myself and Freud, we were all atheists.\NWe all thought religion was foxhole religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.12,0:08:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a fear of dying, now you get God.\NSee, so we all rejected that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so that was a false God that we rejected.\NAnd the mistake was in assuming,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've disproven the reality of a false God,\Nthat doesn't mean that a true God doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the...\Nwhere they were thinking that it stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.29,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Galileo at 485.\NYou see Hegel at 425.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had to...\NFor this book, I've had to review all the great philosophers over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's really been fun.\NIt's like going back to childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.32,0:09:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, other kids were out playing stickball.\NAnd I was sitting there reading Plato and Socrates
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.\NUh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Little did I realize...\Nthat some 70 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be what I'd be writing about.\NWhat I've been writing about the last couple of months
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is what I was reading when I was 12 years old.\NThe dialogues of Plato.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.03,0:09:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.\NSo, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.73,0:09:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Gaiety, where they all are.\NThe great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.53,0:09:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippocrates, the father of medicine, 485.\NYou know, Homer, the Iliad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.29,0:09:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,William James, the great philosopher Kant.\NKepler, the great astronomer, Kepler.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.28,0:09:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And Machiavelli.\NAnd then, in the middle of all these incredible people,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.21,0:10:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got Milton, you've got Newton, 499.\NYou've got Plato at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Plotinus jumps the whole thing.\NWhen you read Plotinus, it's really a spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.55,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very spiritual.\NYou have Sophocles at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.76,0:10:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you've got the great names of history.\NCollectively, the greatest minds that ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.65,0:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's recalibrate the books of the greatest ones.\NWe have permission to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist before the sun.\NAll right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.10,0:10:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Collectively, the great books of the Western world\Ncalibrate over, as they are on the board,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.26,0:10:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate over 460, 465, 470, 475, 470, 475.\NOkay, if we remove Karl Marx,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.81,0:10:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the Western world\Nwill calibrate over 470.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,475, 480, 485, 490.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.91,0:10:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we have to take Marx out of there.\NWe got a new world, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.28,0:11:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he got in there at 130.\NThe difficulty with Marx is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.40,0:11:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that it set up, you know, and gave energy,\Npolitical energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dualistic concept of perpetrator and victim.\NAnd perpetrator and victim is a poisonous...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Perpetrator and victim,\Nlet's do perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The projection of perpetrator and victim\Ncalibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.60,0:11:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 130, 135.\N135.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.56,0:11:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how perpetrator and victim\Nis so pervasive in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.26,0:11:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as a sociological, political,\Nphilosophic theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.10,0:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's them, society out there,\Ncausing each thing to be what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.72,0:11:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing each thing is,\Nwhat it is because it's radiating forth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.58,0:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,into physicality, its own energy.\NThat which calibrates at 120
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,will live in and create an environment\Nthat is concordant with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.45,0:12:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing is being what it is\Nbecause of its own karmic momentum
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the potentiality coming into actuality.\NNothing is being caused
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.27,0:12:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,by anything outside of itself.\NEverything is being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of what it is.\NNot by virtue of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.13,0:12:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how serious an error that is\Nin the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.39,0:12:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is what it is\Nby virtue of what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.02,0:12:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's no karmic responsibility,\Nwould there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.90,0:12:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of something.\NWe're all victims of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.60,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of evolution.\NWe're all victims of the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of the weather.\NWe're all victims of having a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all victims of being human.\NI'm a victim of getting older.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Little people are victims of childhood.\NYou want to play the victim game,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.17,0:13:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,ad nauseum.\NThen everything is the victim of everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore nothing is responsible\Nfor its own actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.34,0:13:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is somebody's fault out there.\NThat justifies vilification,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.78,0:13:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which justifies,\Nwhich justifies hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So if by their fruits you shall know them,\Nthat distortion of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.88,0:13:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,has a very serious fallout\Nin my lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's caused.\NThink how many people died
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.19,0:13:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in the various revolutions,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.99,0:14:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I, 10 million died\Ndue to the distortions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth.\NWorld War II, millions more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Mayo's experiment,\NChairman Mayo's experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.36,0:14:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,experiment, experiment,\Nexperiment, cost the lives
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.81,0:14:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of 30 million people who died\Nof starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,30 million people died of starvation\Ndue to that distortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The vilification of that\Nwhich is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.35,0:14:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions more die.\NSo to be unaware of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.20,0:14:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,serious distortion\Nthen brings about death
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.20,0:14:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and destruction.\NThat's why we say peace is the automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.20,0:14:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of truth.\NWar is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.36,0:14:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of falsehood.\NWhether it's cultural war, physical war,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or any other kind of war.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.13,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what we can learn from\Nthe great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.45,0:15:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellectual basis of\Ndemocracy then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nmany centuries old.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been refined,\Nthought about, argued
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by the best minds\Nin all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.68,0:15:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For thousands of years.\NIf somebody has a better
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.51,0:15:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,idea, I'd like to hear it.\NThe best
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.73,0:15:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,minds throughout history\Nhave evolved as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.73,0:15:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the structure of the world\Nthat we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in the highest calibrated country in the world.\NHighest calibrated country
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.31,0:15:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world.\NSo, to have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.31,0:15:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,respect then for that which is\Nintegrous, calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.31,0:15:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,460, 470, 480,\Nthat is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.37,0:15:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That is integrity.\NSo we reverence integrity in all of its forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the snow today\Nis beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.63,0:16:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and incredible music,\Nand people who devote their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.69,0:16:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to God and to service to others.\NWe respect beauty because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the revelation of divinity.\NEventually, we go
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.25,0:16:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond form itself.\NWe are no longer dependent
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on the aesthetics of form.\NWe go beyond the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.12,0:16:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetics of form.\NAnd then one sees
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from everything\Nradiates divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.53,0:16:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything is equally beautiful.\NYou discover that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.66,0:16:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,first in weeds, I think.\NYou're going by a weed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly,\Nlook at this weed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.30,0:16:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an incredible piece of sculpture.\NShow me any human sculpture
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.30,0:16:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that reaches the perfection.\NYou see the weed standing there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.30,0:16:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and its structure is absolutely\Nperfect and balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.30,0:16:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you see\Nthe divinity of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're going to go to a practical\Napplication of all of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.81,0:17:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if you think it's just for your spiritual enlightenment.\NOr fill up the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NWhat's the practicality?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is sort of a jump on the book\Nthat I'm finishing up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.29,0:17:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, every country you can calibrate\Nthe energy level of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.29,0:17:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the government and the leader.\NAnd they can be quite divergent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.32,0:17:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a very\Nintegrous people, the people of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.32,0:17:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a seriously pathologic leader.\NYou can have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,loving, wonderful people\Nand their bureaucracy is rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.55,0:17:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are great.\NThe bureaucracy is horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain countries you don't drive your own car in.\NBecause everybody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.65,0:18:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The slightest thing that happens, they're going to put you in jail\Nand blackmail your family back home
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.65,0:18:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for 10,000 to get you out of jail.\NSo we don't drive our car there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We leave it at the border.\NSo the leader's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.87,0:18:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are integrous.\NBut the bureaucracy is rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.03,0:18:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fall of Russian communism,\Nsame thing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The gangsters took over, bureaucracy.\NCertain countries in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.32,0:18:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the people are wonderful.\NSome of them have great leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But the self-feeding bureaucracy\Nis so rotten through and through
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't get integrity.\NSo you get three different numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So diplomacy, when it fails,\Ncosts the lives of millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We went back to World War I.\NWe went back to World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.32,0:18:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how each one was due to a failure\Nof understanding other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.74,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We antagonized the rest of the world\Nby coming on superior
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:19:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and smugly superior.\NTry to sell them our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.00,0:19:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the error?\NWell, it isn't exactly what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.80,0:19:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another one,\Nbut I guess that other one is in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have what I call the raw scale\Nwith universal applicability.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.37,0:19:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is, this is called us.\NOops, us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.69,0:19:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called us\Nand this is called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can turn it around.\NThis can be us and that can be them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.69,0:19:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For convenience, this is us\Nand that's them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.45,0:19:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's take it into international diplomacy\Nand see how we could have prevented
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.45,0:19:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all the wars that have happened\Nso far in recent history.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.48,0:19:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We start out, we draw a line.\NI've got lines all drawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You start out with where are you.\NYou're at, this is USA, 421.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.48,0:19:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now who do you want to deal with?\NWho do you want to deal with?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to deal with a culture\Nthat is at 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:20:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to sell them your program\Nof 421
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.50,0:20:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're only at 221\Nand it's going to fall on its butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.50,0:20:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not talking the same language.\NYou try to sell 421
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.01,0:20:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to a country that is at 125.\NYou try to sell 421
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to 125,\Nwhich is poverty and craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They care about everybody having a vote.\NI mean, it's an idiotic idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.36,0:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people are too dumb to vote.\NThere's all countries
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.60,0:20:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where nobody went as far as third grade.\NEverybody's illiterate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Their problem is food.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.47,0:20:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Their problem is food.\NThen you deal with countries that are run by
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,regimes that are run by rage.\NAlright, so you begin
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the\Nusefulness of this as a tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.26,0:20:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones I have at home all have\Nlittle dotted lines with an arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.26,0:21:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have a dotted line.\NYou have your dotted line come down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.26,0:21:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the arrow goes to whatever\Nyou're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be your company\Nand this is your customer base
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.36,0:21:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're heading for.\NThis could be your advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the group you're heading for?\NSo we've been calibrating advertisements.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.69,0:21:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, a lot of them make you go weak.\NHow they sell whatever they're selling
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.69,0:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because every time\Nthere's one pharmaceutical
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.69,0:21:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got the most horrible looking woman on the front.\NWhen you calibrate her, she's 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.69,0:21:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I open a psychiatric magazine\Nthere's this ugly looking woman
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.69,0:21:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating at 130 and I hate their product.\NI hate their product.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.64,0:21:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's awful.\NSo you say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.83,0:21:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,where are we and where are they?\NAnd now
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't make these gross\Nmiscalculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.44,0:22:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There was\NAdolf Hitler at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.81,0:22:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed the non-aggression pact.\NWhat's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.48,0:22:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Comes back to 110 Downing Street\Npeace in our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.09,0:22:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner did he sign this pact with Hitler\Nand I'll tell you what Hitler was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.09,0:22:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler was thinking\Nwhat a stupid ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He was thinking\Nwhat a stupid ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.39,0:22:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean really.\NAnybody who ever grew up in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.32,0:22:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,knows better than that.\NThe non-aggression pact with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.46,0:22:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah right.\NThe minute your back is turned
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.84,0:22:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,gotcha.\NIt's to get you to drop your defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.07,0:22:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The feint.\NSo the non-aggression pact
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.13,0:22:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the inability\Nto see through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.51,0:23:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I\Ntry to bring up naivete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.44,0:23:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside\Nbecause spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.44,0:23:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people with spiritual naivete\Nare famous for the blindness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.44,0:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of their downside.\NOh everybody's good and sweet
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.98,0:23:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we just believe in their goodness and sweetness\Nthat's when the truck hits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.24,0:23:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because that which is against\Nwhere you're at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.24,0:23:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking for an opening\Nand your blindness is their opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.94,0:23:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,10 million people died\Ndue to that opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.94,0:23:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're not just talking about theory.\NNot talking about theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're just good to them\Nthey'll be good to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.39,0:23:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what's gonna happen if you're good to them.\NAnd gloat over your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.64,0:23:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,stupidity.\NSo to be spiritual doesn't mean to be dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.92,0:23:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean to walk around\Nthe world this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.77,0:24:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that happen?\NTry opening this eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.77,0:24:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha\Nand Jesus Christ and Krishna
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.89,0:24:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't say it doesn't exist.\NHe said don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.89,0:24:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have anything to do with them.\NAvoid it. Do not oppose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.89,0:24:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not go to war with it.\NBut don't deny it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.28,0:24:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid anything that makes you go weak\Nwith kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.64,0:24:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he said.\NMake sure I don't go weak. Don't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.80,0:24:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so\Nin the book we calibrate the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.34,0:24:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of a number of countries\Nand now you see
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.37,0:24:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're dealing with\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.37,0:24:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,here's a country\Nat a level here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it's dealing with a country here\Nyou cannot go across this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.37,0:25:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NYou cannot come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.63,0:25:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name?\NThe guy that got us into World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.23,0:25:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamberlain.\NYou see Chamberlain is coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.68,0:25:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a\NI think he's about 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.71,0:25:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He's around in there.\NBut look what he's dealing with here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.57,0:25:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's saying\NI'm going to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.57,0:25:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to trust you.\NLook what this guy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.02,0:25:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't trust anything below 200\Nexcept that it's going to eat you, kill you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.02,0:25:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or sell you short.\NAlright so if he knew beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.40,0:25:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to meet with a guy\Nwho calibrates here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.40,0:25:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NWhat a different story history would have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.14,0:25:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nyou can use this in relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.49,0:25:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I?\NWho am I talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.92,0:26:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I? What am I studying?\NWhere's my business?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.34,0:26:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my customer base?\NI'm the university
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.61,0:26:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,where are my students?\NI'm the professor, where is everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.61,0:26:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So to talk meaningfully then\Nmost people that are very
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.45,0:26:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,deviated from truth, far from truth\Nare off into sophistry
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.45,0:26:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,rationalization\Nand rhetoric.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.68,0:26:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We think\Nbecause they're sort of puffed up with pride about it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.64,0:26:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that democracy because it's so superior\Nand wonderful everybody should just go
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.64,0:26:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,gaga over it.\NWhy should they go gaga over that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.79,0:26:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which they don't even understand and don't even\Nvalue?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.11,0:26:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we antagonize the world to ourself.\NIt isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.62,0:26:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of what you are\Nbut how you present that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.62,0:26:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the president do the same thing.\NHe's thinking that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.62,0:27:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the truthfulness of the content\Nshould hold the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.62,0:27:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Aristotle said\Naside from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.54,0:27:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,sophistry there is rhetoric.\NWhat's useful about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.73,0:27:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,rhetoric is the realization that\Nyou have to anticipate where your audience
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.73,0:27:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is at, not just where you're at.\NIf you want to know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.96,0:27:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my opinion of Bush's downside\Nhe knows where he's at
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.96,0:27:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but he doesn't present himself.\NHe doesn't contextualize himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.47,0:27:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me most politicians\Nare not adept at
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.47,0:27:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how to contextualize\Nwhere they're coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.47,0:27:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One simple sentence would\Ntake them out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.42,0:27:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict they're into.\NOne simple sentence that would recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.42,0:27:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so they spend all their time defending\Nthemselves on the level of content
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.42,0:27:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and they contextualize\Nthemselves with just one or two facts
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.61,0:28:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole field changes.\NYou don't have to defend yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.25,0:28:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth doesn't need to defend itself.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.60,0:28:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of contextualization\Nis crucial to survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.60,0:28:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Survival of our world.\NSo it's not just a philosophic position.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.88,0:28:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In your own spiritual evolution\Nit's necessary to be able to discern
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.88,0:28:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.\NTo avoid getting polarized
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.01,0:28:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in positionalities.\NSo what you do is you align
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.01,0:28:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself with the highest truth\Nthat you are able to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.01,0:28:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and live your life\Nin accordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.20,0:28:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to give up positionalities\Nbecause there's only
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.20,0:28:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,different ways of looking at\Nthe same phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.20,0:28:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The same phenomena.\NThey appear differently
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.81,0:28:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from two different perspectives.\NThat doesn't mean they're two different realities
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.81,0:28:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of life.\NSo the difficulty with life
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the present world\Nis that appearance is not essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.41,0:29:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is not essence.\NAppearance is not essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.82,0:29:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That which one is innately\Nis not what it appears
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.72,0:29:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to be out there.\NThat's one of the great values
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.84,0:29:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of calibrating levels of consciousness\Nand that's why we did
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.88,0:29:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a thousand for this book\Nbecause not everybody is able
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.88,0:29:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to do kinesiology and very often\Nwhat we try to do then
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.97,0:29:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is to calibrate the things\Nof ordinary life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.97,0:29:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual teachers,\Nreligions,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.26,0:29:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,various belief systems,\Nvarious things in our culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.48,0:29:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,various architectural styles,\Nthe media,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.48,0:29:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,movies, books,\Nwriters, art.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.80,0:29:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to cover the entire\Npanorama of human life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.28,0:29:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and recontextualize it\Nthroughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.41,0:30:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an experience\Nin all of its complexities
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.79,0:30:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NNo wonder I'm tired out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.16,0:30:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I wonder\Nwhy I was pooped the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.78,0:30:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to calibrate\Nthe Encyclopedia Britannica.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.07,0:30:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course each thing\Nleads to something interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.07,0:30:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and new.\NSuddenly in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.07,0:30:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of eating a fork full\Nof scrambled eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.74,0:30:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly get,\Noh yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.74,0:30:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,valor.\NValor is different than curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.74,0:30:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you get what valor means.\NYou got a whole couple more paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.54,0:30:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how the book goes on forever.\NBecause one thing leads to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.05,0:31:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we wanted to\Nhave an announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.05,0:31:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we're going to\Nhave questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.82,0:31:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a break.\NBut I think we tried to cover
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.62,0:31:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that is necessary to know.\NIt's not necessary to know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.23,0:31:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we said it today.\NNo thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.90,0:31:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I pledge no thinking, Doctor.\NHail to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.80,0:31:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I choose instead to be\Nthat which I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.80,0:31:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I choose to be a prayer\Nand by my existence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.80,0:31:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,do I bless thee.\NWhile they're setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.05,0:31:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to have Nico do a chant.\NLotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.00,0:31:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Sutra in Sanskrit.\NAnd he's going to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.58,0:32:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,just by himself.\NAnd while he's doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.06,0:32:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody that has to do anything else\Ncan do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.75,0:32:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico.\NI would suggest just relax into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.16,0:32:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This requires no thinking on your part.\NAnd close your eyes if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.96,0:33:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now we're going to have a chat with you.\NHello, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.49,0:33:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Michael here.\NI'm here to see Lord Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.49,0:33:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to thank you\Nfor your Friendship and for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.49,0:33:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,support you've shown me over the years.\NAnd to make sure you have the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.76,0:33:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,best possible time in your lives.\NSo, as you only have one thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.88,0:33:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I would suggest that we make a\NBible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.88,0:34:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is great to do.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.84,0:35:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.87,0:37:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Nico.\NConsciousness, that annoying time between naps.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.20,0:38:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.82,0:38:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks very much for everything today.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.36,0:38:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Page 304 of your book, you talk about a personal meeting with a sage,\Nand you're the only one I know, so I came here,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.76,0:38:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't know how it works,\Nbut it seems like everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.32,0:38:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,everything else is thinkingness,\Nso if you can flare what's going on over there this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.34,0:38:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me embrace you, sir, formally.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.64,0:38:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been formally embraced.\NExcellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.32,0:38:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I came.\NI know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it takes.\NThe energy's there for...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.50,0:38:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I had a subjective experience recently with meditation\NI wanted to ask you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.94,0:38:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I closed my eyes,\Nand I did your very simple...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.54,0:39:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I did my very simple thing of looking at the Fahs genes,\Nlooking past them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.10,0:39:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've waited it out.\NUsually I don't get anything for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.24,0:39:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just sit there for 25 or 30 minutes,\Nand I sat there about that long,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.28,0:39:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there was this ground that materialized.\NIt was like a sort of a deep space photo,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.26,0:39:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,something like that,\Nand I had the sense when I was looking at it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.80,0:39:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was seeing only maybe, you know,\N90 degree angle of it or a certain view.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.94,0:39:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I was definitely outside the picture,\Nand then I tried to rotate it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.10,0:39:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know,\Nbecause you're always talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.50,0:39:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,be the context, be the field,\Nbe the whole, everything of what you're seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.40,0:39:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tried to rotate it 360,\Nand then suddenly my sense of self,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.76,0:39:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,except for a very thin and persistent pinprick of consciousness\Nlike deep in my head,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.16,0:39:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was like in this field,\Nand there was no body,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.34,0:39:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing at all there\Nexcept the very nagging sensation in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.34,0:39:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm wondering what's going on there,\Nlike,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.02,0:39:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what level I'm at.\NI didn't feel bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.92,0:40:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like,\NI actually felt like I was led to this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.74,0:40:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I kind of looked back at myself,\Nand I got the distinct sensation that nothing was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.12,0:40:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,like what I consider to be me.\NI was looking back,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.27,0:40:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was like deep space, too.\NYou became space, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.35,0:40:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NWell, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.21,0:40:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the identification with the content dissolves,\Nand you begin to identify with the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.79,0:40:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why I say spiritual work is really the way you are in the world,\Nthe way you contextualize yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.57,0:40:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you see yourself.\NYou begin to see yourself impersonally.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.77,0:40:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to realize that life is impersonal.\NIt's subjective,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.00,0:40:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but even the subjective is a quality\Nthat is not a personal possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.79,0:41:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of itself,\Neverything is happening of its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.86,0:41:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you stop personalizing it as an I and a that, huh?\NSo what you're doing is going into a type of meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.52,0:41:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,where you begin to disidentify with the content,\Nand you become at one with the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.39,0:41:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that you're the field, not the content of the field.\NThat meditative awareness then begins to translate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.46,0:41:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,into,\Ninto contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.04,0:41:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can experience it intensely in meditation,\Nbut it's the translation into contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.68,0:41:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I recommend contemplation more than meditation.\NMeditation is very informational.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.16,0:41:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You discover various things,\Nbut then as you open your eyes and walk around,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.16,0:42:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the samadhi leaves,\Nand you're left with what is your
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.95,0:42:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,prevailing level of consciousness.\NContemplation is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.25,0:42:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a supplication to God at all times,\Nto be that which is the expression of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.82,0:42:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as this form,\Nbut then the form only becomes an expression of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.32,0:42:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it takes the person out of it.\NSo contemplativeness is a way of life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.48,0:42:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the meditative experience was going from identifying with me,\Nthe I,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.80,0:42:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the person itself as content,\Nand experiencing yourself more as context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.09,0:42:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NI mean very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.54,0:43:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your help.\NI'm looking forward to your new book.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.78,0:43:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for it too myself.\NYou can imagine how cheerful society is about having the truth revealed about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.29,0:43:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean that's what they say.\NTell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.74,0:43:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then leave town several experiences in my life and I shared them with friends\Nand my husband but I have not been able to talk about them with anyone who could
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.27,0:44:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,really give me a more concrete answer about so many years ago probably eight I\Nwas working in the library high school library and it was my habit to go there
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.75,0:44:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I was meditating about four hours a day at the time for about three months and\NI'd been meditator for about 25 years anyway but I would go and read the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.88,0:44:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Upanishads for about 15 minutes before the students would come so I had this\Nquiet time well it got so as I was reading them I was having this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.64,0:44:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible joy and I understood them not that I could write a comment but I\Nunderstood them on a very wonderful level
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.15,0:44:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and\NI
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.45,0:44:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they gave me so much joy, and I couldn't wait to get in there at lunchtime\Nbefore the students would come and read my panachat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.46,0:44:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know which one I was on, whether, and I agreed with everything it said, wholeheartedly.\NAnd in the middle of my reading, there was this experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.56,0:45:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a veil had opened up.\NEverything disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.04,0:45:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The library was gone, everything, and I was in this blackness, such a space.\NAnd there were planets and stars coming at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.00,0:45:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I interpreted, that they were light, but I felt I was in the middle of the universe.\NAnd at first, there was me, but I had completely disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.48,0:45:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, how's all this here in my heart?\NI said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.60,0:45:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the right side of...\NFrom the left side of me, it said, all this was made by you, for you, and because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.56,0:45:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, oh.\NAnd we're in this note today.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.18,0:46:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I accepted that, and then there was this, it just kept going on,\Nand the planets and the stars kept coming faster and faster at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.00,0:46:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as though I was going toward them and they were coming toward me.\NAnd I was in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.92,0:46:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How did I get in the middle of the universe?\NI was in a library.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.76,0:46:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So finally, I felt this incredible loneliness.\NIt was pit, lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.05,0:46:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, I'm the only one in the universe?\NSo we're heading for the void, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.25,0:46:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.67,0:46:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I became more lonely and perhaps frightened.\NAnd I said, where's God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.43,0:46:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I wanted to see God, but he wasn't there.\NAnd with that thought, at the time I was thinking, where's God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.48,0:46:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of abyss opened up underneath me, at the same time as, and the veil closed.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.35,0:47:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel like I blew up.\NYou didn't blow anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.13,0:47:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For months after that, I lived in a lot of bliss.\NI had no ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.55,0:47:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My desires were all gone.\NI was just happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.55,0:47:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd laugh at rocks.\NThere was no fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.75,0:47:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was friendly.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.17,0:47:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it faded.\NIt's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.21,0:47:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So?\NWhat I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.19,0:47:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the question?\NDid I blow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.21,0:47:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I not go through?\NDid I lose my courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.65,0:47:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.\NSee, where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.39,0:47:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really gone forever?\NWhere you were was the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.29,0:47:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you how you know when you're in the void.\NThe difference between nothingness and allness is the element of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is in.\NIn the allness of divinity, the presence of love is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.10,0:47:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It melts everything with its infinite grace, its infinite power.\NThere's no feeling of loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.91,0:48:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the loneliness means you're in the void.\NYeah, it was the universe of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.40,0:48:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where the pathway of negation will take you.\NThere are certain teachings that teach you to negate love.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.85,0:48:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, love is one of the qualities of divinity.\NAnd it's a serious error.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.74,0:48:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God.\NAnybody who's had a near-death experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.48,0:48:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here have had a near-death experience?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.24,0:48:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most telling qualities is you're melted by the exquisiteness of the presence of a love beyond which you've ever even imagined.\NSo you explored the void to see how far it would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.09,0:48:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And you found out that it leads to nothingness.\NLoneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.81,0:48:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut you were in a high place to be checking out the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.12,0:49:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, sir.\NYou were in a very good, you know, advanced stage because of the years of meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.74,0:49:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NSo through the meditation, you were going through the pathway of negation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.52,0:49:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this, not that, not this.\NSo the next step is to realize that divinity is allness, not nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.66,0:49:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.30,0:49:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, to understand God, you see, it's through the misunderstanding of love.\NFrom the ego's viewpoint, love is an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.20,0:49:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're going through the pathway of negation, which is let go of attachments and aversions,\Nyou would then begin to see love as an attachment and something that would be standing in your way of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.02,0:50:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's emotional attachment on a dualistic basis.\NLove is a quality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.48,0:50:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NSo if you negate the reality of love, you will end up in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.72,0:50:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of divinity includes love, but not dualistic love, a love of a me for a love of a you.\NAnd if you leave me, I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.63,0:50:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll own you and possess you.\NLet's see what's the shortcut for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.22,0:50:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortcut.\NWhat is the shortcut?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.08,0:50:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I still meditate about the power of the day.\NYeah, I want you to pray to the love of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.80,0:50:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to the love of God.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.68,0:50:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway of devotional non-duality is non-duality without devotion can lead you into the pathway of negation and bring you to the void.\NBut it's the devotion to it that takes you into the divinity of the presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.37,0:51:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence is also without form, but it includes the quality of love which just wipes you out.\NIt wipes you out in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.66,0:51:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the divinity is love and the completeness of love.\NSo the difference between the two is the void will take you to a feeling of loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.25,0:51:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite state brings you to a state of completion.\NIn the state of completion, there's nothing you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.80,0:51:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how you can tell a true spiritual teacher from a false one, which is one of the lessons of today.\NA true teacher needs nothing because a true teacher already is all there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.98,0:51:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you offer him power, he'd say,\NWhat would I do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.22,0:51:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a closet full.\NIt would be a drag, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.05,0:51:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Control over others, power over others, influence over others.\NI mean, who would want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.50,0:52:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the fact that it left you incomplete, but the void is a very high space to get into.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.45,0:52:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows a lot of work on your part, more than this lifetime to get that far.\NWell, is it coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.68,0:52:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, my life after...\NUnless God hates you, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.52,0:52:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You pissed me off, girl.\NI guess because it faded, because I lived for three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.58,0:52:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stunning space to be in.\NIt's a very, very stunning space.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.22,0:52:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To the naive person, they think this is it.\NBecause it has all the qualities of a finale, there's a finality to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.74,0:52:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something about it that is the ultimate.\NIt is.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.88,0:52:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the ultimate void.\NThat's not necessarily where I want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.64,0:52:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not where you want to go.\NYou want to go to allness rather than nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.78,0:52:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right.\NAt age three, I looked at that at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.50,0:53:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NAt age three, that was the confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.92,0:53:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Allness versus nothingness.\NExistence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.72,0:53:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So devotion would be the...\NYeah, pray to the love of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.18,0:53:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to the love of God, yeah.\NWhich is where I started when I was a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.74,0:53:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NJust hanging with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.70,0:53:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hanging with the love of God, see?\NYou've done enough of the not this and not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.36,0:53:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a lot of that.\NYou already know you're not this and not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.56,0:53:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I did that a lot.\NYou're all that is, so now just be inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.14,0:53:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.32,0:53:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So divinity is exquisitely beautiful.\NIt's exquisite beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.66,0:53:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite gentleness.\NAnd it's loving to the point that you feel like you could melt in it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.24,0:53:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and die this moment and you would be complete.\NYes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.48,0:53:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you're there.\NWhen if you're suddenly expired, it would be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.14,0:53:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, yes.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.94,0:53:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're already complete.\NThere's nothing more you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.12,0:53:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, exactly.\NYou got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.98,0:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NThank you for answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.92,0:54:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple.\NWell, it wasn't because for like eight years I feel like I've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.03,0:54:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt's a very stunning space to be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.11,0:54:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The void is a very stunning space.\NI felt like I've been in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.85,0:54:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you were suffering from void shock for a number of years.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.95,0:54:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.07,0:54:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.11,0:54:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.23,0:54:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.31,0:54:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.49,0:54:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.61,0:54:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.71,0:54:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.79,0:54:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.97,0:54:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.07,0:54:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.15,0:54:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.19,0:54:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.31,0:54:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNow, that's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.53,0:54:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's a joke.\NIt is.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.65,0:54:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stunning.\NAnd it leaves you shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.93,0:54:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my husband.\NHe was with me through this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.09,0:54:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you feel shocked like you have somehow failed.\NYes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.11,0:54:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.57,0:54:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I blew it.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.77,0:54:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel like you blew it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.47,0:54:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the space is very, very impressive.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.27,0:54:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NGod is space.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.49,0:54:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was like...\NIt's very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.67,0:54:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Being part of our space.\NIt's beyond form.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.05,0:54:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond time.\NBeyond location.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.41,0:54:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond personal identity.\NSo, I shouldn't read the punishments anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.95,0:54:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I love reading them.\NI mean, they give my heart joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.65,0:54:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You just do what I tell you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.55,0:54:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.\NI'll start.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.94,0:55:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my teddy bear?\NYour teddy bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.46,0:55:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I need my teddy bear.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.92,0:55:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She scared me.\NI need my teddy bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.82,0:55:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, you meditate on the purr of a kitty and a dog's wagging tail, and it'll\Ntake you from nothingness to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.45,0:55:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take you from nothingness to almas.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.35,0:55:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have a question about God and consciousness.\NAnd here's your teddy bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.19,0:55:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, teddy.\NI was frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.63,0:55:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That lady frightened me.\NWe're okay, teddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.62,0:55:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're okay.\NAre God and consciousness the same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.78,0:55:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what is their relation?\NConsciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.28,0:55:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to write and talk to you at the same time.\NExperientially, out of the unmanifest arises the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.08,0:56:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the manifest arises the manifest.\NOut of the manifest arises the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.40,0:56:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the manifest arises consciousness, which is not different than the energy of life.\NThe light energy of consciousness, life, when it interacts with material matter, spawns
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.33,0:56:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,living, biologic life as we know it throughout evolution.\NConsciousness is without form.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.08,0:56:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's within the subjective experiential.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.59,0:56:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be God manifest to the degree...\NThat is, God as divinity is subjectively experiential as self with a capital S, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.86,0:57:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally unmanifest.\NThere would be no capacity for knowing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.08,0:57:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NWhere's my right arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.59,0:57:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right arm.\NOh, she's hiding behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.46,0:57:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat which was just expressed was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.81,0:57:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI'd never said that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.39,0:57:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you repeat it, please?\NI can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.63,0:57:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.\NTotal consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.94,0:57:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is infinite potentiality, omnipotent.\NOmnipotent, omniscient, omnipresent.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.52,0:57:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a potentiality.\NIt's the God, the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.14,0:58:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the Godhead manifests God as creator.\NBut that's only an actualization of a potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.16,0:58:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest is not bound to become manifest, but out of its potentiality becomes manifest\Nas the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.91,0:58:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the universe, then, is born the capacity for consciousness and awareness.\NThe manifestation of God as consciousness, then, is one of the manifestations of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.24,0:58:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which we share with God.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.10,0:58:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe presence of God within us is knowable by virtue of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.67,0:59:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the expression of God as consciousness, you would not even know that you exist.\NTo be aware that you are is already an expression of divinity as consciousness is experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.77,0:59:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the subjective.\NTo say, to be aware that you are, to know that you are, to say it is taking you out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.36,0:59:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of it already.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.58,0:59:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's knowing.\NKnowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.32,0:59:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NRather than believing, it's knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.32,0:59:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because even to use an intransitive verb like am-ness is already a step down from\Nreality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.00,0:59:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate the statement I am, it's less than the ultimate reality.\NThat which is is beyond all categories, such as beingness, existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.68,1:00:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Am-ness is an intransitive verb, but it's a denigration of the level of the true state.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.16,1:00:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for asking me such a fun question.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.16,1:00:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I sign them all?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.85,1:00:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThere are some Lollapaloozas in the audience, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.02,1:00:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't ask you dumb things.\NI don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.02,1:00:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.02,1:00:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NI would just like to thank you for all your sharing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.02,1:00:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your sharing.\NYes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.02,1:00:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And your giving.\NYou're the most generous teacher I've ever known.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.28,1:00:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody there to be generous.\NYes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.61,1:00:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.61,1:00:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.61,1:00:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.61,1:00:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.35,1:00:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.35,1:00:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.64,1:01:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody there to be generous.\NIts just a condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.64,1:01:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If I an anything to do it, I'll be stingy.\NWake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.31,1:01:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the bear?\NWhere's the king?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.19,1:01:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He's listening in.\NHe's eavesdropping.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.91,1:01:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks that's a microphone dumbbell.\NThat's the wrong end.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.21,1:01:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this way.\NWell.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.59,1:01:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see-\NI can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.15,1:01:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor is necessary to existence.\NWithout a sense of humor, you can't really get along spiritually, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.08,1:01:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humor is the capacity to go outside yourself and laugh at yourself.\NYou laugh at yourself, you're forgiving yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.14,1:01:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're including yourself in and letting it be okay.\NSo the humor of human life is a way of healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.54,1:02:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can laugh at yourself well, you see, because everything's ridiculous.\NLife is a theater of the absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.85,1:02:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read the daily headlines, you realize it.\NToday's madness, you say, I really don't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.54,1:02:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Get some guy on TV, you say, I can't believe this is happening.\NTheater of the absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.83,1:02:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's comical.\NSome spiritual teacher that used to teach me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.18,1:02:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who it is.\NIt's a serious error to take life seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.46,1:02:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think taking life seriously is comical.\NSo you have to get serious about taking life as being comical.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.10,1:03:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Farrah, yeah, golly, whiz.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.83,1:03:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't have a story, I don't have a question, and if you knew me two years\Nago, you'd know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.59,1:03:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You would know what a miracle that is.\NOh, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.47,1:03:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.\NSo you've been through some kind of wondrous transformation, I can see, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.16,1:03:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't even speak, see, that's what happened.\NIt's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.44,1:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.\NIt's not explicable.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.94,1:03:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not explicable.\NIt's a condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.13,1:03:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a condition that prevails.\NThat's why nobody goes through it takes credit for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.30,1:04:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody becomes egoistic about it.\NNobody becomes egoistic or prideful because it is not of the personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.71,1:04:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the recipient of the benefit of it.\NYeah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.45,1:04:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's terrific.\NYes, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.54,1:04:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She's referring him up, so if she wants...\NOh, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.64,1:04:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has to come up.\NI'd be happy to sign their books incognito.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.26,1:04:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Ben Lawden.\NHe tried to get my autograph on a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.95,1:04:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's not me.\Nautograph on a book you saw it okay thank you first of all for being my
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.94,1:05:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual teacher for the last year I've been coming about a year now oh thank\Nyou also from Wisconsin oh wow I've got a question about CEOs you kind of opened
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.71,1:05:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your session this morning talking about female CEOs in my experience I teach\NCEOs and write books for them and I would agree the problem is that 99.9% of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.30,1:05:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the CEOs are men and probably will be for some time I've heard you talk about\NCEOs with a great deal of empathy but you've also said they calibrate as a
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.57,1:05:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,group in the 190s is that right that particular group of corporations was\Nright before Enron was but that was before the big fallout okay before the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.04,1:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,big fallout not a big corporation so I won't even say what they are calibrated\Nat 195 around there
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.70,1:06:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mm-hmm now some of them have been taken over and big corporations that were\Nnon-integrated are now over 200 so a lot of them are now over 200 and going
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.60,1:06:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,through a reconstruction no I think the average I have 100 greatest corporations\Nin the world we have permission to do with the CEOs in fortune 500 resist
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.60,1:06:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,collective consciousness of the CEO\NJohnson the Fortune 500 are over 200
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.12,1:06:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,resists 199... scream one hundred\NJesus there are 1.99 well they were worse than that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.55,1:06:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to do something for corporate America here bleed out the camera on this\None please they were at about 194 195 they were at about 194 they're up to about
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.53,1:06:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,199 okay\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.85,1:07:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what's happening is because the overall field is 207 it's surfacing everything that is less than\Nintegris every day the headline is that something that we once got away with is now being uh focused
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.48,1:07:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a shift of the culture in which the culture is realizing that integrity shows up on\Nthe bottom line yeah it is going through that integrity every day's headline is about the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.24,1:07:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity of some politician some congressman some businessman some corporation right ninth\Ncircuit court of appeals whatever the question is the integrity of judicial bodies even the supreme
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.34,1:08:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,court are they being integrous or are they giving some of us some kind of political bias readout you\Nknow so the integrity of everything
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.21,1:08:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is on the line right now so society where i grew up integrity wasn't on the line\Nyou know you're a democrat voted for roosevelt or you're republican who voted for somebody where it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.32,1:08:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,was eisenhower or somebody uh but integrity wasn't it wasn't the question nobody questioned\Nroosevelt's integrity or eisenhower's integrity nobody questioned their integrity uh it was
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.24,1:08:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know whether they were more one party or the other party but their integrity was not in question\Nwell just here's my my question i guess
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.86,1:08:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you better test that with your wife my question is this and i know that ceos in my 30 plus years\Nof teaching them are probably more open than i've ever seen them before they're getting better and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.82,1:09:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,better and they're more under pressure but i was struck by the the difference between less than 200\Nand more than 200 in your lecture this afternoon and i know ceos are forming corporate governments
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.98,1:09:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,committees they've got the legislation\Nthere's a lot of things that's
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.60,1:09:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,happening but my question is\Nthis I'm just finishing up a book called
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.64,1:09:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the CEO challenge\Nand I'm trying to recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.96,1:09:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole field of management thanks to your\Nteachings and I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.98,1:09:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to write it for CEOs\Nand my question is what is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.96,1:09:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a message that I can\Nhelp give that might help this along
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.98,1:09:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit well you see they're under\Nbrutal pressure yes
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.40,1:09:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,brutal pressure on the bottom line\Nand the stockholders want profits
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.10,1:09:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're under\Nbrutal pressure unless you're made of steel
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.92,1:09:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how these guys withstand it see\NI don't know how they take it
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.94,1:09:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,under brutal pressure\Nby the way I just had a 20 year
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.46,1:09:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,client who got fired\Nas a CEO after
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.16,1:10:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,five years and I talked to him\Nthe other day he said I am so relieved to be
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.40,1:10:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that job oh it's a terrible\Njob he said I can't tell you how happy
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.32,1:10:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I am to be out of that job\Nit's a very tough job
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.88,1:10:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're being pushed to the\Nedge of non-integrity all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.98,1:10:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,yes yes you're really under\Nfire a slight move in
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.02,1:10:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this direction moving the\Nstock look at what you all make
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.41,1:10:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you got stock options\Nthe move of a
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.47,1:10:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,dollar you just made a fortune\NI don't know how they do it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.93,1:10:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is there a message is there\Nhow can I raise their level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.75,1:10:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,CEO is a tough\Nassignment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.03,1:10:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because on an ethical\Nviewpoint you are
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.97,1:10:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the responsibility\Nof stewardship
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.43,1:10:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the stewardship\Nso you have a responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.56,1:10:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,big style\Nthey need
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.09,1:11:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion\Nthey need support of everybody in the organization
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.01,1:11:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they need the love\Nand compassion it's a heck of a job
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.44,1:11:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a very difficult job\NI wouldn't want to be CEO of anything frankly
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.85,1:11:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,me either\Nokay thank you very much
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.61,1:11:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a whole subject in itself\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.59,1:11:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and one I'm quite interested in too\NI'm quite interested in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.07,1:11:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulty of the businessman\Nhaving to show a profit
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.73,1:11:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same time remain\Nintegrity
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.29,1:11:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that's right\Nthat's right
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.69,1:11:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much\Nin the book I was saying about
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.01,1:11:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how people hate success\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.52,1:11:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they really hate it when you're not doing anything\Nthey really hate it when you're not doing anything
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.74,1:11:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,with a vengeance and especially they hit big companies but one of the you want me\Nto sign something going broke you know the the vilification of capital well
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.62,1:12:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,capital as I said this morning is that money in the bank it's a bright idea in\Nthe head from that bright idea in the head multi-billion spawned forth and the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.00,1:12:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,vilification of corporations people forget that most of these the wealth of\Nthese corporations was accumulated over hundreds of years you compare your
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.88,1:12:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime inner earnings and you say compared to that corporation look how\Nmuch there they've been in business over 200 years well you put away money at 4%
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.16,1:12:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for 200 years the company the corporations outlive all of us Ford was\Nestablished in 1903 Brock where is Brock Brock hey I don't know where he is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.58,1:12:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway Brock got me a list of corporations\Nyou know I don't know where he is anyway Brock got me a list of corporations
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.44,1:12:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,many of the giant corporations actually started in the 1700s well 250 years later\Nso the corporation is huge and powerful not because it's voracious but because
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.94,1:13:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's been integrally busy for 250 years so that recontextualize is it you want\Nme to sign something please I don't know where you sign this what is in here your
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.50,1:13:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,lunch\NI'm going to sign here I don't know if it's gonna start out on there yeah Thank
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.99,1:13:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You\Nmusic
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.04,1:13:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,写\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.41,1:13:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nme
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.93,1:13:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you mean by psychic. You mean esoteric?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.93,1:13:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean consciousness?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.93,1:13:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean mind?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.93,1:14:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Experimenting like what?\NWell, I practiced. I started practicing my psychic nature by seeing that if I was capable
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.93,1:14:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of seeing that which is unseen, non-linear, and I started to practice with friends and\Npeople with names, just using the third eye. I read a couple of books, Edgar Cayce and
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.34,1:14:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,others, and I found that...\NYou mean psychism?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.34,1:14:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.34,1:14:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I found that actually it was a function of practice and silence, but I found that I could\Nsee people's names, dead people, live people.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.45,1:14:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,People I had no knowledge of.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.45,1:14:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And incidentally, when this happened, whenever this happened, the other person said, well,\Nyou know, fine, can you see my grandmother's name who died 27 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.68,1:15:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd I would take a look at it, and I would literally see her and ask her for permission
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.80,1:15:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to know her name.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.80,1:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She would give it to me.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.80,1:15:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And this person would right away be sort of...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.80,1:15:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of astonished or amazed, and then quickly covered up...\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.12,1:15:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...as if nothing had happened at all.\NSo the reason I'm bringing all this up, and this happened, this went on for about six
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.12,1:15:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or nine months...\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.12,1:15:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...is today you mentioned, you were talking about kundalini energy...\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.57,1:15:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...and potentiality...\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.57,1:15:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...and how we had no, we in effect had no power over whether or not we were going to\Nexperience this movement of kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.40,1:15:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NSo what you're talking about is psychic ability...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.52,1:15:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\N...and it can be practiced and learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.52,1:16:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been practiced since the days of Mesopotamia.\NAnd so those are psychic abilities.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.54,1:16:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They occur spontaneously.\NThey occur spontaneously as a consequence of the kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.57,1:16:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be pursued for their own ends, which is, so the ancient spiritual teachings are\Nto avoid the cities, S-I-D-D-H-I-S, to avoid pursuit of the cities, and to avoid considering
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.80,1:16:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,them to be personal.\NThat is you performing that, because it is not you performing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.28,1:16:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the kundalini energy doing what it does of its own nature, having nothing to do with\Nyou personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.28,1:16:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo there are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.38,1:16:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One is kundalini energy...\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.38,1:16:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...which does what the world would consider possible.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.96,1:16:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...which the world would consider paranormal of its own.\NThen there is psychism, which is a pursued skill.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.60,1:16:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Two different things.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.79,1:17:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So what was I experiencing?\NYou were pursuing the skill.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.43,1:17:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.91,1:17:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.91,1:17:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NJust practicing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.91,1:17:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an altered state of consciousness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.91,1:17:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Like learning distant viewing, you know, or out-of-body projection, you know.\NI went to Monroe Institute and learned how to go in and out when I want, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.94,1:17:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What was...\NI want to share what I found out.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.94,1:17:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really interesting.\NAt the same time, I had a lot of dreams and many prophetic dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.97,1:17:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd in one particular week back in 84, two major airliners went down, one in Japan and
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.70,1:17:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,one in Dallas.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.70,1:17:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was like on a Monday, and I had this dream.\NAnd it was so powerful, I called my father who was a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.31,1:17:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd I said, I just want to tell you about this dream I'm having.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.31,1:17:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, it was about sitting in the rear of the plane in a safe place and so forth.\NHe said, well, that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.31,1:18:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But the two planes went down, and on Friday, I called him back because I had all this doubt.\NDid this really occur?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.01,1:18:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I really have this dream?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.01,1:18:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I recognized later that it's like this is the ego covering up anything other than\Nlinear reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.49,1:18:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd I had to literally go to him on Friday and say, did I have this conversation with
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.49,1:18:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you on Monday?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.49,1:18:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I not talk about these dreams?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.49,1:18:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, yes, you did.\NYou know, he confirmed it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.49,1:18:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBut in my mind, to me, it was the ego covering up, you know, anything that's not within
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.49,1:18:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,its realm.\NIs that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.65,1:18:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI don't know about that interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.65,1:18:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYou see, we live in a world of infinite potentiality, any one of which, combined with intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.94,1:18:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,combined with karma, plus favorable circumstances, may materialize.\NIt's one of 10 million options that could materialize.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.64,1:19:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner or later, one of them's going to materialize.\NThey materialize.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.81,1:19:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.81,1:19:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Lincoln saw his own death.\NYou know, it happens very often.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.81,1:19:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?\NAbraham Lincoln saw his own assassination in a dream, et cetera, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.81,1:19:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.19,1:19:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just curious about what you thought about the idea of the ego covering all this\Nup.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.19,1:19:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you mean by that.\NWell, the same thing happened when I came up with a name, and the person across the
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.87,1:19:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,table from me was quite shocked by it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.17,1:19:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But then suddenly covered up and said, oh, well, yeah, that's my great-grandmother's\Nname who died 27 years ago, and we never met, who I haven't thought about in 22 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.41,1:19:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat's the question?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.41,1:19:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it.\NWell, is this the ego covering up this astonishment, this surprise?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.41,1:19:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did they cover this up?\NWell, just a statistical likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.41,1:19:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NThat's why people are impressed with psychic powers.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.41,1:19:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.41,1:20:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI see your grandmother reading the tea leaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.22,1:20:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.26,1:20:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother used to read the tea leaves.\NShe did.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.32,1:20:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAppreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.32,1:20:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I see your grandmother reading the tea leaves.\NYes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.83,1:20:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI have a few burning questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.62,1:20:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIf I tell a lie, what is the energetic repercussion of that in the hologram?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.43,1:20:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens to the person that I'm lying to?\NWhat happens to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.43,1:20:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it affect all that is?\NWhen an untruth has happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.43,1:20:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're never going to affect all that is, you know, because you're an infinitesimal\Npart of what all that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.43,1:21:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But if everybody does it, then the consciousness level of mankind goes up or down.\NActually, everybody knows unconsciously when they're being lied to.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.74,1:21:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yeah, closer.\NI want you to be on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.44,1:21:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NYou need to be where you're with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.44,1:21:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, everybody...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.44,1:21:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.44,1:21:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.\NThis side or this side.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.44,1:21:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, everybody knows unconsciously when they're being lied to or just...\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.33,1:21:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that shows you something interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.82,1:21:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when I calibrated the advertising industry as an industry, it was below 200.\NFirst of all, think how much more, you know, how much more powerful an advertisement would
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.65,1:21:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,be.\NI used to have hyperacidity, and I take the purple pill, and now my stomach feels fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.61,1:21:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's an actress, so she's lying.\NWell, I don't think it's somebody who had terrible hyperacidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.72,1:22:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They took the purple pill, and now they feel great.\NOne would be convincing unconsciously, and the other you know is crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.88,1:22:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NI used strong language.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.16,1:22:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NThe other is...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.29,1:22:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Advertisements would be powerful if they were real.\NAnd if they...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.29,1:22:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we were calibrating, I think I'm gonna, at the last minute, put in maybe half\Na page of advertisements, you know, like the MSN Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.29,1:22:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he's so stupid looking, how he would sell anything.\NThat is the dumbest commercial I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.29,1:22:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, Whiskas is hilarious.\NWhiskas shows his little, you know, cat and shows this big stag, you know, and then the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.65,1:22:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,kitty stares down the stag and starts to chase the stag, and the stag runs off.\NYou calibrate that, it's over 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.29,1:22:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you gonna ask me?\NWell, you know how...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.29,1:22:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the fact that our thoughts, every one of our thoughts ripples through the universe.\NYes, it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.68,1:23:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ripples through the hologram.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.28,1:23:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So my thought would be that a lie would have some kind of a repercussion for the\Nhologram.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.46,1:23:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what about a white lie?\NNo, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.46,1:23:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, the different levels of lies.\NExactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.46,1:23:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You could text someone.\NWell...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.46,1:23:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, because there's...\NJesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.46,1:23:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, you could text someone.\NWell, you know, because there's...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.46,1:23:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, you could text someone.\NWell, you know, because there's...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.46,1:23:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, you could text someone.\NWell, you know, because there's...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.46,1:23:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is asking a couple different questions.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.46,1:23:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,See, below 200 is force, it's not power.\NSo an itty-bitty lie at energy field 180, its impact on all of life is insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.46,1:23:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who lies at level 520 is gonna have some serious karmic consequences.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.46,1:23:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.46,1:23:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.46,1:23:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.06,1:23:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.06,1:23:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.60,1:23:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.60,1:23:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.60,1:23:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.14,1:23:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
