Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.21,1:24:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.21,1:24:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.21,1:24:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI mean, in certain realms, murder is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.26,1:24:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you kill 10 or 12 people,\Nso what does that make you, a big shot?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.30,1:24:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You get in there with the big boys to kill 10 million,\Nnow you're playing with the big dealers.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.82,1:24:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The big dealers, 10 million here, 20 million there.\NHere, Mayo, 30 million die of starvation
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.91,1:25:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,due to Marxist BS, due to totalitarianism.\NPeople want to sell us that paradigm of reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.37,1:25:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.\NWell, I've also noticed there are different kinds of lying,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.71,1:25:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,like the sin of omission.\NWe know the intention behind it, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.47,1:25:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You just reveal it all.\NThere's two intentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.03,1:25:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,One is to hurt other people.\NThat is a different karma than to protect yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.09,1:25:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we lie just to cover ourself.\NThat's not really injuring anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.04,1:25:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's lowering our own internal integrity.\NThen sometimes we lie to injure somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.76,1:25:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To bear false witness is a rather grave karmic consequence.\NIt's to bear false witness against your neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.20,1:25:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I don't like to hear the severe polemics of political extremes,\Nbecause to falsely accuse somebody else
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.06,1:25:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is, you know, violating one of the commandments.\NIt's not to bear false witness against yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.86,1:26:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to bear false witness against your neighbor,\Neven if he's running, you know, on the other party.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.86,1:26:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still a grave error, see.\NYou don't have to vilify chocolate to be the champion of vanilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.86,1:26:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wish the politics would learn that.\NSo if one is of a more high consciousness, like, say, 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.50,1:26:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you tell a little white lie,\Nwhat we call a white lie to protect yourself...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.50,1:26:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get away with white lies as you move on up.\NSo even an exaggeration would be considered...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.10,1:26:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, white lies are...\NWhy are you worrying about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.27,1:26:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to try and sell me a used car, or what?\NWhat else?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.99,1:26:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to try and sell me a used car.\NWell, that discussion of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.97,1:26:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the implications of it in business, you know,\Ncame up over the weekend with the visitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.97,1:26:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I had me discuss the impact of that in business.\NWell, that was one of my burning questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.30,1:27:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one is...\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.30,1:27:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\NWhen I have the desire to pray for another person,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.30,1:27:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,how do I do that without being in a positionality or thoughts\Nor in some way judging their experience or their life
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.30,1:27:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm wanting to pray for, you know...\NYou want to change them, really.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.30,1:27:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.\NYou're trying to change their spiritual destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.30,1:27:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to help them, send them energy, whatever you want to call it.\NYeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.30,1:27:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to undo their negative karma, or what?\NWell, I guess I'm wondering, how do I connect with another being with prayer?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.46,1:27:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you want to connect with them?\NMaybe I'm stuck in the new age.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.00,1:27:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to connect with any dead people. Do you?\NNo, no, no. Not dead people. Live people.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.00,1:27:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, live people.\NYeah, like I want to pray for somebody who is...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.00,1:27:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got you.\N...having problems in their life or, you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.00,1:27:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you stay to the highest good, then you're doing well.\NYou see, because what you see as disaster is frankly to their highest good.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.23,1:28:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I do have that caveat in my prayer.\NI say to the highest good...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.74,1:28:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.74,1:28:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the person's highest good, you can see they're speeding rapidly towards the bottom in disaster.\NAnd that's just what their higher self is holding for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.63,1:28:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to prevent the disaster, you just, you know, delayed their salvation.\NBecause it was only by hitting bottom that they are going to rise to the top.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.52,1:28:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, trying to change it out there, you know, is being quite naive.\NBecause, like you said, your perception may not be what it's about at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.52,1:28:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like we applaud people's success, and that success is, you know, what's going to take them to the bottom.\NWe see that happen all the time to celebrities and various people.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.52,1:29:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it still worthwhile to pray for them then?\NI don't know. That's what your motive is, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.05,1:29:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you wouldn't be asking the question.\NYou're trying to change people, influence them, control things.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.88,1:29:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're messing around with other people's karma and stuff.\NOn the other side is the gooderism, and on the other side is genuine spiritual commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.01,1:29:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to find out where you are and all that.\NIt feels like I have a high motivation of just sending them energy of help and caring.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.49,1:29:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they ask you to do that?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.49,1:29:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.\NThat's a big one going down.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.14,1:29:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's different answers at different levels.\NBut I get you're about to transcend that level.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.14,1:29:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you wouldn't be asking me the question.\NProbably.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.14,1:29:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're trying to influence other people.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.14,1:29:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're already getting that intuitively.\NThat's why you're asking me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.14,1:29:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NLet them worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.46,1:30:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let their own karma and their own be what it is.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.78,1:30:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention to be loving towards them, of course, is great.\NAnd the last question I wanted to ask you is, okay, it's beyond the third dimension that we're in right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.90,1:30:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Third dimension?\NIs that just a new age thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.09,1:30:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the 9th or 10th generation.\NAre you still back in the third?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.69,1:30:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead, sweetheart.\NI'm just kidding along with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.69,1:30:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.69,1:30:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The past, present, and future at some point becomes one.\NWe're not in time anymore, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.69,1:30:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAt some point.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.69,1:30:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So from that place, I'm assuming it's all the past, present, and future become one somewhere in the future.\NOne somewhere in the field of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.69,1:30:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they don't become one.\NBut they are one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.76,1:31:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't become anything.\NWell, this is in reference to the fact that calibrating...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.94,1:31:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, they're not three separate things that then become one.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.94,1:31:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're three separate things to begin with.\NIn other words, just no time.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.94,1:31:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no past, present, or future.\NIn the space that we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.94,1:31:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But with the tool of kinesiology, we are only to calibrate present statements.\NWhat is?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.94,1:31:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo past, present, and future are all one beyond here anyway, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.04,1:31:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt's too much to think about.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.04,1:31:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you mean.\NI guess I'm trying to ask why we can't calibrate the future if the future is the same...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.28,1:31:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it has no existence.\NIt has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.28,1:31:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know that based on your information.\NBut if the future is the same as the present and the past...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.28,1:31:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're confusing it intellectually.\NYou're playing with it conceptually.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.28,1:32:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't a conceptual thing.\NIt's obvious that the future has no reality because otherwise there would be no evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.63,1:32:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.\NThere would be no spiritual merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.58,1:32:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the universe is waiting for you to collapse the wave function.\NThrough the Heisenberg principle, intention itself, consciousness itself already takes
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.22,1:32:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality into actuality.\NThe minute you look at a thing, it's already changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.64,1:32:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot see the same thing twice because you're looking at it has already changed it.\NSo, therefore, no future could possibly be known because it depends on an infinite number
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.56,1:32:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of decisions and choices.\NSo that's why you can't predict future events.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.66,1:32:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen in the year 5083 is all in your head.\NNobody can predict what's going to happen in the year 5083.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.80,1:32:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible.\NBecause the future is only a potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.92,1:33:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Free choice means that you are where you are within the infinite field by virtue of choice.\NYou choose this.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.10,1:33:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You choose this.\NYou choose this.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.10,1:33:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You choose this.\NIf the fate was of all of the universe was already set, predetermination, there would
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.69,1:33:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,be no point to life anyway.\NSo predestination is just an intellectual concept.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.56,1:33:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.\NIt's not the same as karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.72,1:33:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're not the same.\NYou got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.26,1:33:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because divinity, once you understand the nature of divinity, you realize that predestination\Nand divinity are not compatible.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.93,1:33:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity cannot be divinity and still be the source of predestination unless you project\Nforward into the future and now the present becomes the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.49,1:33:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?\NI don't know what that meant, but it sounded good.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.39,1:33:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat should shut her up, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.39,1:34:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you get into intellectual constructs.\NIt's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.60,1:34:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, she's got a lot of good questions.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.60,1:34:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NA question about resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.72,1:34:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it best to resist nothing or is there nothing to resist?\NThat's a conundrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.16,1:34:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you resist nothing?\NThere'd be nothing to resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.80,1:34:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by resisting nothing?\NYou mean don't resist anything, not nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.56,1:34:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't resist anything that comes up.\NYeah, true.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.68,1:34:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe other way is to resist everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.45,1:34:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.44,1:34:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my main question would be that I tried the kinesiology testing.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.57,1:34:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She tried kinesiology.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.57,1:35:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBut I would like to know how would I get more consistent answers or more
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.36,1:35:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consistency?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.40,1:35:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to know how would I get more consistent answers or more clear answers.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.40,1:35:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on what the basic problem is.\NWe'd have to do like a short individual workshop with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.16,1:35:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned this morning, the capacity to do it, first of all, not everybody has\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.90,1:35:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, it's limited to probably 10% of the population anyway.\NThe intentionality, the intention behind the question has to be integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.35,1:35:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I would always say in the name of the highest good, you can't have any personal interest.\NYou can't have any personal interest in the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.11,1:36:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the background in the setting has to be appropriate.\NAnd you may need special training.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.91,1:36:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the easiest thing in the world for some people.\NSome people it becomes very easy and other people it's quite difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.91,1:36:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Susie teaches it to a lot of people and she usually finds out what's wrong.\NSometimes they're holding the arm too straight.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.91,1:36:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say a lot of people resist the arm going weak.\NIt's a very transitory weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.91,1:36:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ape in us thinks it's falling out of a tree.\NSo you get it, especially in macho guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.91,1:36:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute the arm goes weak, they're unconsciously falling out of a tree and their ape comes\Nup with strength, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.91,1:36:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And they get high answers for everything, you know?\NMy dog calibrates over 1,000, 2,000, 3,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.52,1:36:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We get letters all the time.\NMy dog calibrates over 900, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.59,1:36:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.41,1:37:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a technique.\NIt has to be learned.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.41,1:37:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there's a kinesiologist.\NA lot of times a holistic practitioner.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.41,1:37:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's actually a kinesiologist that you can see for a private consult.\NDo you ever read Dr. Diamond's book?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.44,1:37:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you need education.\NYour Body Doesn't Lie by Dr. Diamond is a classic in the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.47,1:37:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just need more education.\NAlso, have you heard of a contemplative outreach, Father Thomas Keating?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.23,1:37:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NCentering prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.23,1:37:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We spoke up there.\NWe were with Father Keating a few months ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.77,1:37:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe's a big guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.20,1:37:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's over six foot tall.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.20,1:37:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Look up there.\NI'm high, brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.20,1:37:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.20,1:37:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWe spoke at the St. Benedict's Monastery up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.20,1:37:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Met with monks.\NAnd we did a public thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.43,1:38:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWe did a public thing in the city hall there in Aspen.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.43,1:38:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a beautiful monastery.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.56,1:38:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful place.\NSo centering prayer and contemplative outreach.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.56,1:38:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NHe's the champion of centering prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.56,1:38:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Which got him into a little trouble with the church itself, too.\NBut he handled it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.48,1:38:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The classic religion distrusts the mystic.\NAnd I represent the mystic.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.57,1:38:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I spoke to the monks, they didn't say anything.\NI don't know if they were praying silently inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.33,1:39:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The worry is that without ecclesiastic guidance, a person could go wrong.\NAnd that it sees authority as protective of the naive soul that could wander off into
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.54,1:39:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,wide avenues.\NThere's a certain reality to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.69,1:39:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't discredit it.\NCertain reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.69,1:39:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we get a lot of bizarre letters out there.\NWhere people do get derailed.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.39,1:39:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI know Father Keating.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.96,1:39:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI enjoyed him, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.92,1:39:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we had dinner with him, didn't we?\NAye.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.48,1:39:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye.\NEven for someone like yourself, how susceptible is kinesiology to the Luciferic?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.41,1:40:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Luciferic means, too, is the temptation of power.\NI remember when the Luciferic came.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.57,1:40:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-verbally, as a knowingness, power for its own sake was what it was about.\NI don't know what that's got to do with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.56,1:40:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Of getting, having a Luciferic influence give you the wrong answer.\NWell, that would be the intentionality of the person using it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.88,1:40:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who seeks to use it for gain, for power.\NUsually, the misuse of it is to verify positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.04,1:41:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,People want you to calibrate something they've already got a really screeching positionality\Nabout.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.51,1:41:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NTo verify that their candidate is better than this candidate's.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.86,1:41:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Or this spiritual teacher is better than that spiritual teacher.\NThey have a vested interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.96,1:41:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'd say Luciferic use is a vested interest.\NA vested interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.30,1:41:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Something to gain by it.\NInstead of a tool, it's something to gain by.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.71,1:41:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if you have positive intentions of the Luciferic energy trying to get in there\Nand giving you wrong answers?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.71,1:41:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the whole point of being Integrist.\NSo, because both are over 200 and the question is Integrist, the Luciferic does not prevail.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.21,1:41:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you say, in the name of the highest good.\NSee, the Luciferic has a vested interest in one answer or the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.42,1:41:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Luciferic is certainly not interested in one answer or the other.\NIt's certainly not interested in what is the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.18,1:42:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not interested in the stockholder.\NIt's interested in exercising its stock options.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.50,1:42:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not interested in the welfare of the stockholder.\NSo, yes, I understand what you're saying from a hypothetical viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.36,1:42:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked at myself quite a bit.\NCan I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.42,1:42:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NCan I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.42,1:42:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a hug.\NI'm going to put some devious burp behind me.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.87,1:42:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's a very good question.\NVery good question.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.32,1:42:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows he's not asleep.\NNo, you see he's not into denial.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.71,1:42:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He realizes that there's things out there that are antithetical to spirituality\Nand purity and integrity, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.71,1:42:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it comes looking for your chinks.\NYes, it does look for your chinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.59,1:43:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.88,1:43:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NUm.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.88,1:43:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is regarding the idea of the soul moving up through evolution\Nlike a cork in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.56,1:43:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NNow, it's, I mean, personally, I feel I can see it in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.56,1:43:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And you mention in your book that suddenly a soul, for one reason or another,\Nwill put down a heavy foot and start backpedaling.
